{
  "texts": [
    "For counting hedges, boosters, pronouns as personal markers, and the type-token ratio, an online tool called Text Inspector has been used.",
    "According to Text Inspector, it analyses your text based on the metadiscourse markers first listed by Hyland (2002), then modified by Bax et al. (2019).",
    "Hedges, boosters and pronouns are markers of meta-discourse.",
    "The type-token ratio is a statistical calculation done separately by this tool.",
    "The selection of two distinct types of texts, one authored by a student (\"STUDENT\") and the other generated by GPT-4 (\"GPT\"), ensures a comparative analysis between human-generated and AI-generated content."
  ]
}